main event: A civilian in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania reported seeing a large, whitish ball moving towards the city on October 10-11, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting was reported by Mr. J.J. Spotz, who worked at the Willow Grove Naval Air Station.
The object was seen moving in the area of South Lane towards Philadelphia, Pennsylvania around 8:00 PM.
The report indicates that an FTD Form 164 was expected to be received to provide more details about the sighting.
The report was extracted from the D.C. report of October 10-11, 1966.
The Air Force's Project Blue Book was investigating the sighting, but stated they did not have enough information to evaluate it.
witnesses: Mr. J.J. Spotz, civilian from Willow Grove Naval Air Station
